  "Ribozymes are RNA molecules that can catalyze chemical reactions, demonstrating that RNA can serve as both genetic material and enzyme, potentially acting as the first self-replicating molecule": "",
  "Ribozymes are ancient ribosomes found in fossil records, which represents a common but incomplete view of how these ribozymes dynamics operate": "",
  "Ribozymes are RNA molecules with catalytic activity, showing that RNA can both store information (like DNA) and catalyze reactions (like protein enzymes). This dual capability supports the idea that early life could have relied on RNA alone.": "",
  "A cancer researcher discovers that the telomeres (repetitive DNA sequences at chromosome ends) in tumor cells are maintained by an enzyme called telomerase, keeping these cells immortal. In normal cells, telomeres shorten with each division. Why is telomerase activity in cancer cells significant?": "",
