  "Telomerase repairs all types of DNA mutations in cancer cells": "",
  "Telomerase makes cancer cells resistant to all chemotherapy drugs": "",
  "Normal somatic cells lack telomerase, so telomeres shorten with each division until the cell stops dividing (Hayflick limit). Cancer cells reactivate telomerase, maintaining telomere length and achieving unlimited replicative potential.": "",
  "A virologist discovers that a newly identified virus has an RNA genome that is directly translated by ribosomes upon entering the host cell. Another virus has RNA that must first be converted to DNA by reverse transcriptase. How do these two viral strategies differ in terms of nucleic acid biology?": "",
  "The first is a positive-sense RNA virus whose genome acts directly as mRNA; the second is a retrovirus that uses reverse transcriptase to make DNA from its RNA template, which then integrates into the host genome": "",
